data.description: Perfect property for those who want to live in nature and close to town. California's coastal redwoods are an ecological treasure, and when you're in the hills rising up above the colorful west Sonoma County towns of Occidental and Bodega, you're in the thick of them. Bask in cool solitude at the end of the lane and hear nothing but the birds, critters, and maybe some of your own music? The hand-built redwood home could use some TLC, but once it's spruced up, it will be a wonderful haven. Multiple outbuildings are ready to serve your needs and those of your family and friends, including a lovely art studio overlooking the neighbor's giant open meadow, a large office or workspace, and more. Lots to see and feel here on Joy Woods Way, where you're about 10 minutes to charming Occidental, even closer to Bodega, less than 15 minutes to beautiful Bodega Bay & the coast and under 20 to artsy & foodie Sebastopol.
